main event: An unidentified flying object was observed in Massapequa, New York in 1967.
interesting points: The object was described as a bright, silvery object that made a whistling, high-pitched sound.
The object appeared to be solid and sharply defined, and it changed brightness at times.
The object was observed for about 5 minutes before being obscured by a passing cloud.
The observer compared the object's brightness to that of a bright star.
The observer provided a hand-drawn sketch of the object, which appeared spherical with a trail behind it.
sighted object: a bright, silvery spherical object with a trail
photographs: no photographs, only a hand-drawn sketch
